= sdavids-docker-healthcheck
Sebastian Davids <sdavids@gmx.de>

== java/http

* GraalVM does not support `linux/arm64`
+
https://github.com/oracle/graal/issues/5872
+
[,console]
----
$ cd java/http
$ scripts/docker_build.sh
8.332 Error: Missing CAP cache value for: NativeCodeInfo:BuiltinDirectives:PointerToInfo:char
8.332 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8.339                         0.2s (2.8% of total time) in 13 GCs | Peak RSS: 0.47GB | CPU load: 2.05
8.340 ========================================================================================================================
----
+
.java/http/Dockerfile
[,dockerfile]
----
FROM ghcr.io/graalvm/native-image-community:21.0.2-muslib AS healthcheck

FROM nginx:1.27.1-alpine3.20-slim AS http_server
----
+
⇓
+
.java/http/Dockerfile
[,dockerfile]
----
FROM ghcr.io/graalvm/native-image-community:21.0.2 AS healthcheck

FROM nginx:1.27.1-bookworm AS http_server
----
+
[,console]
----
$ cd java/http
$ scripts/docker_build.sh
$ scripts/docker_start.sh
$ scripts/docker_health.sh
healthy 0
----
+
Alternatives:
+
** https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/guides/build-static-executables/[Build a Statically Linked or Mostly-Statically Linked Native Executable]
** https://github.com/graalvm/container/issues/89#issuecomment-1857395921[gcompat]

* Update `README.adoc` w/ musl size; still `4.0M`?
